Implement every function marked `support` in `ObjectiveTree/00.5-support-full-ncursesw-API/missing-functions.md` as `terminal::Window` API and `Window::Impl` wrappers, keeping functions grouped in `Window.h` by the same invisible-island.net man page URL headings from the decision file and adding any missing URL group before its declarations.

In `Window.h`, public `Window` declarations return `void` unless they return a `Window`; failures are handled by assert/exception rather than public `int` or `bool` status returns. Near-duplicate ncurses names collapse to the same C++ member name by stripping ncurses-only `w`, `mv`, and `n` affixes where normal overloading makes the signature distinct, following the existing `addstr` style. Every supported ncurses function appears in the trailing declaration comment, e.g. `void addstr(Position pos, char const* str, int n); // mvwaddnstr`. Add one short single-line comment above each declaration explaining non-trivial behavior, parameters, and side effects; trivial appending output such as `addstr` and `printw` does not need such explanation. Replace `int y, int x` with `Position pos`, and replace `int height, int width` or equivalent dimensions with `Dimension size`.

In `Window.cxx`, each newly added public `Window` member simply calls the same-named `impl_` function with the same parameters. `Impl` functions may return the underlying ncursesw return type; when the public wrapper receives a non-void result, store it in a local `res` and assert success with `ASSERT(...)`.

In `Window::Impl`, translate `Position` and `Dimension` back to integers and call the exact ncursesw function named in the `Window.h` trailing comment, returning that ncursesw result. Each `Impl` function must have a comment containing the relevant invisible-island.net man page URL, followed by one blank `//` comment line, followed by a short excerpt/paraphrase from that man page explaining what the function does.
